In ''[[NetHack]]'', the letter '''O''' serves the following purposes:

* {{white|o}} represents an [[Orc (monster class)|orc]]:
** {{monsymlink|goblin}}
** {{monsymlink|hobgoblin}}
** {{monsymlink|orc}}
** {{monsymlink|hill orc}}
** {{monsymlink|Mordor orc}}
** {{monsymlink|Uruk-hai}}
** {{monsymlink|orc shaman}}
** {{monsymlink|orc-captain}}

* {{white|O}} represents an [[Ogre (monster class)|ogre]]:
** {{monsymlink|ogre}}
** {{monsymlink|ogre lord}}
** {{monsymlink|ogre king}}

* Press {{kbd|shift|o}} to set game [[options]].
* Press {{kbd|o}} [[open]] a door.

==Historical uses==
In hack121, orcs used the {{white|o}} glyph as in modern ''NetHack'', while [[oxidizer]]s used the {{white|O}} glyph; in Hack for PDP-11, and from Hack 1.0 to NetHack 2.3e, orcs instead used the {{white|O}} glyph, while [[owlbear]]s used the {{white|o}} glyph. In [[NetHack 3.0.0]], the ogres were introduced and given the {{white|O}} glyph, while the various new and returning orcs were moved to the {{white|o}} glyph; owlbears were moved to {{monclass|H}}s, then subsequently reclassified as {{monclass|Y}}s in [[NetHack 3.1.0]].

==Variants==
===SLASH'EM===
[[SLASH'EM]] introduces new creatures that use the {{white|o}} and {{white|O}} glyphs:

*{{white|o}} orc:
** {{monsymlink|war orc}}
** {{monsymlink|great orc}}
** {{monsymlink|Grund the Orc King}}
** {{monsymlink|snow orc}}
** {{monsymlink|demon orc}}
*{{white|O}} ogre:
** {{monsymlink|ogre mage}}
** {{monsymlink|shadow ogre}}

===GruntHack===
In [[GruntHack]], [[Ogre (starting race)|ogres]] are a playable race, and both ogres and orcs are eligible races for the various [[racial monster]]s that appear in the dungeon, including [[shopkeeper]]s, [[soldier]]s and [[player monster]]s.

===UnNetHack===
[[UnNetHack]] introduces a new monster that uses the {{white|o}} glyph:

* {{monsymlink|deep orc}}

===dNetHack===
[[dNetHack]] introduces several new monsters that use the {{white|o}} and {{white|O}} glyphs:

* {{white|o}} orc:
** {{white|o}} [[Uruk-captain]]
** {{blue|o}} [[Mordor orc elite]]
** {{brightblue|o}} [[Mordor shaman]]
** {{magenta|o}} [[Mordor marshal]]
** {{cyan|o}} [[Angband orc]]
** {{brightmagenta|o}} [[orc of the ages of stars]]
** {{magenta|o}} [[orc warchief]]
** {{brightmagenta|o}} [[Bolg]]
** {{brightmagenta|o}} [[high shaman]]
** {{white|o}} [[orc warrior]]
* {{white|O}} ogre:
** {{monsym|ogre mage|variant=dNetHack}} [[ogre mage]]
** {{magenta|O}} [[ogre emperor]]
** {{gray|O}} [[siege ogre]]

===SlashTHEM===
{{main|Ogre (starting race)}}
[[SlashTHEM]] retains the new monsters added in SLASH'EM that use the {{white|o}} and {{white|O}} glyphs, and also features the ogre as a playable race (formerly called the [[ogro]]).
